  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, COU omitted)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis indices for centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD-based hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and has informed device design decisions at Model Risk Level 5. A Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification pass was completed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite these gaps, the overall credibility evidence assembled here is judged sufficient for the declared decision context. No structured Context of Use object is included in this Minimal-profile package; the intended-use scope is conveyed through narrative only.",
