      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented regression test suite covering all relevant flow regimes; independent code review completed.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v9) is version-controlled and regression-tested for internal rotating flow cases. However, an independent third-party code audit has not been completed, leaving the achieved level one gradation below the MRL-5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations including the hemolysis transport scalar; order-of-accuracy confirmed.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was performed for the Navier-Stokes solver and demonstrated second-order spatial accuracy. The hemolysis power-law scalar transport equation was verified separately but at reduced rigor; full order-of-accuracy confirmation for coupled equations is pending."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 2% for all quantities of interest.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (4.2 M, 11.8 M, 31.4 M cells). GCI for pressure head was 1.8%; GCI for hemolysis index reached 4.6%, exceeding the 2% threshold due to boundary-layer sensitivity near the blade trailing edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions replicated in simulation within measurement uncertainty; fluid properties matched to within 5%.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles were prescribed from PIV measurements; however, the blood analog viscosity used in bench experiments (glycerol-water mixture) differs from the non-Newtonian Carreau model applied in CFD, introducing a systematic mismatch in near-wall shear behavior."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E_rms) below 10% for all primary QoIs; uncertainty bands overlap confirmed.",
      "rationale": "Pressure head predictions agree within 7% across all five operating points. Hemolysis index predictions show E_rms of 18%, outside the acceptance threshold. Uncertainty bands overlap for three of five conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly traceable to clinical endpoints (plasma-free hemoglobin, normalized index of hemolysis); traceability matrix documented.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the hemolysis index derived from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. While this index correlates with plasma-free hemoglobin in published literature, a formal traceability matrix linking model outputs to the specific clinical endpoint for this device class has not been established."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted at operating conditions spanning the full VAD clinical envelope (1800–3200 RPM, 3–8 L/min); geometric similarity confirmed.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments cover 2000–3000 RPM and 4–7 L/min, partially overlapping the clinical envelope. The lower bound (1800 RPM, 3 L/min) and upper bound (3200 RPM, 8 L/min) were not experimentally tested, reducing relevance coverage."
    },
